li.p:
We see that
\left[\begin{array}{rrr|r} 1 \amp 3 \amp 1 \amp -8 \\ -2 \amp 1 \amp 5 \amp 9 \\ 0 \amp 2 \amp 2 \amp 2 \\ \end{array}\right] \sim \left[\begin{array}{rrr|r} 1 \amp 0 \amp -2 \amp 0 \\ 0 \amp 1 \amp 1 \amp 0 \\ 0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 1 \\ \end{array}\right]\text{.}
Since this is an inconsistent system, there are no vectors \xvec satisfying the equation.

In the same way, we have
\left[\begin{array}{rrr|r} 1 \amp 3 \amp 1 \amp -8 \\ -2 \amp 1 \amp 5 \amp 2 \\ 0 \amp 2 \amp 2 \amp -4 \end{array}\right] \sim \left[\begin{array}{rrrr} 1 \amp 0 \amp -2 \amp -2 \\ 0 \amp 1 \amp 1 \amp -2 \\ 0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \\ \end{array}\right]\text{.}
This shows that \xvec=\threevec{-2}{-2}{0} + x_3\threevec{2}{-1}{1}.

The matrix that defines T is
A = \left[\begin{array}{rrr} \vvec_1 \amp \vvec_2 \amp \vvec_3 \\ \end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{rrr} 2 \amp -1 \amp -1 \\ 1 \amp 1 \amp -2 \\ \end{array}\right] \sim \left[\begin{array}{rrr} 1 \amp 0 \amp -1 \\ 0 \amp 1 \amp -1 \\ \end{array}\right]\text{.}
This shows that the solutions to T(\xvec) = A\xvec = \zerovec are \xvec=x_3\threevec{1}{1}{1}.

We first find weights c and d such that \twovec{1}{0} = c\twovec{1}{1} + d\twovec{-1}{1} by constructing the augmented matrix
\left[\begin{array}{rrr} 1 \amp -1 \amp 1 \\ 1 \amp 1 \amp 0 \end{array}\right] \sim \left[\begin{array}{rrr} 1 \amp 0 \amp \frac{1}{2} \\ 0 \amp 1 \amp -\frac{1}{2} \end{array}\right]\text{.}
This shows that \twovec{1}{0} = \frac12\twovec{1}{1} - \frac12\twovec{-1}{1}. Therefore,
T\left(\twovec{1}{0}\right) = A\twovec10 = \frac12 A\twovec11 - \frac12A\twovec{-1}{1}= \twovec{1}{-2}\text{.}

In the same way, we find that
T\left(\twovec{0}{1}\right) = \frac12A\twovec{1}{1} + \frac12A\twovec{-1}{1} = \twovec{2}{0}\text{.}
This gives the matrix A=\left[\begin{array}{rr} 1 \amp 2 \\ -2 \amp 0 \\ \end{array}\right].
